The paper focuses on using deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for event detection in videos, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses encoding methods and concept descriptors, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of CNNs for feature extraction and classification is also related to machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
